summary: An Ordinance approving and confirming the assessment and assessment roll of Local Improvement District No. 2791 for the improvement of West Dakota Street, from Fifty-second Avenue Southwest to Fifty-sixth Avenue Southwest, and certain parts of certain other streets and avenues; all in the City of Seattle, by grading, curbing and providing for the necessary surface drainage, under Ordinance No. 33410, and levying and assessing the amounts thereof against the several lots, tracts, parcels of land and other property as shown on said roll, establishing a Local Improvement Fund.
